The '''Botswana Football Association''' ('''BFA''') is the governing body of association [[Football (soccer)|football]] in [[Botswana]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1717/editorial/2011/05/21/2495780/botswanas-football-taken-to-the-next-level-the-zebras-are |title=The mystery behind the rise of Botswana football |publisher=Goal.com |date=2011-05-21 |accessdate=2013-11-15}}</ref> and controls the national football team. It is an affiliate of [[FIFA]], [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]] and the [[Council of Southern Africa Football Associations|COSAFA]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bfa.co.bw/about-bfa/who-we-are.html|title=Who we are - BFA|last=Admin|first=BFA|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en-gb}}</ref> 

National football leagues include the [[beMOBILE Premier League]], [[First Division North]] and [[First Division South]].

== History ==
In 1966, the Botswana National Football Association (BNFA)<ref name=":0" /> was created, before the name was changed in 1970 and the BFA officially founded. It was first affiliated to the CAF in 1976, and then with FIFA in 1978.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cafonline.com/en-us/memberassociations/botswanafootballassociation/Home|title=CAF - Member Associations - Botswana Football Association - Home|last=Football|first=CAF - Confederation of African|website=www.cafonline.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref>

