{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Gorse Lane | nickname = | country = England | image =Grantham_Cricket_Club.jpg | location = [[Grantham]], [[Lincolnshire]] | establishment = 1941 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1994-present | club1 = [[Lincolnshire County Cricket Club|Lincolnshire]] | date = 16 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/502.html Ground profile }}
'''Gorse Lane''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Grantham]], [[Lincolnshire]]. It was constructed from scratch when the London Road ground was sold to Safeway. Opened for junior cricket in 1991, the club began using the field a year later.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/502_misc.html Other matches played on Gorse Lane]</ref> [[Lincolnshire County Cricket Club|Lincolnshire]] first played at the ground in the 1994 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] against [[Northumberland County Cricket Club|Northumberland]]. To date the ground has held 5 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/502_mint.html Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on Gorse Lane]</ref> In 1996 they played their first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match at the ground against [[Cumberland County Cricket Club|Cumberland]]. From 1996 to present, the ground has hosted 20 Minor Counties Championship matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/502_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Gorse Lane]</ref>
The ground has also held a single [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match in the [[2000 NatWest Trophy]], which saw Lincolnshire play the [[Netherlands national cricket team|Netherlands]],<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/502_a.html List-A Matches played on Gorse Lane]</ref> a match which Lincolnshire won by 95 runs.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/69/69748.html Lincolnshire v Netherlands, National Westminster Bank Trophy 2000 (2nd Round)]</ref>
Gorse Lane is the home ground of Grantham Cricket Club.
