{{Use Australian English|date=February 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}} {{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Jack Manski Oval | nickname = | logo_image = | image = | image_size = 220px | location = Golf Links Drive, [[Kirwan, Queensland|Kirwan]], [[Queensland]] | coordinates = {{Coord|19|19|6|S|146|42|44|E|display=it}} | broke_ground = | opened = 13 August 1984 | owner = Brothers Leagues Club | operator = Brothers Leagues Club | surface = [[Grass]] | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | former_names = | tenants = [[Townsville Blackhawks]] (2015–present) | seating_capacity = 4,000 | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = Rectangular }}
'''Jack Manski Oval''' is a sporting venue situated in the suburb of [[Kirwan, Queensland|Kirwan]] in [[Townsville]], [[Queensland]], [[Australia]]. Predominantly used as a [[rugby league]] ground, it is the home ground of the [[Townsville Blackhawks]], who play in the [[Queensland Cup]]. The ground is also used by the Townsville Brothers junior and senior rugby league teams.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blackhawkstsv.com.au/game-day/about-jack-manski-oval/|title=About Jack Manski Oval - Mendi Townsville & Districts Blackhawks RFLC|publisher=|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>
==History== Originally based at Queens Park and, later, Gill Park, the Townsville Brothers rugby league club purchased 20 acres of land from Kern Brothers Earthmoving in the early 1980s in [[Kirwan, Queensland|Kirwan]] to develop a new clubhouse and playing fields in the suburb.
On 14 May 1983, the venue was officially named Jack Manski Oval, in honour of Jack Manski, a club official who worked for the club for over 40 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://websites.sportstg.com/club_info.cgi?c=0-2240-23759-0-0&sID=390060|title=History - Brothers Townsville Junior Rugby League Club - SportsTG|website=SportsTG|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>
The ground was officially opened on 13 August 1984, with Brothers playing University and winning in all four grades.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brotherstsv.com.au/about-us/history|title=Originally formed as Brothers Rugby League Club Townsville in 1922 - History - Brothers Leagues Club - Townsville|website=www.brotherstsv.com.au|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>
On 10 September 2014, it was announced that the [[Townsville Blackhawks]] were admitted into the [[Queensland Cup]] for the 2015 seasons and would play their home games at the venue.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.qrl.com.au/news/2014/09/10/qrl-announces-townsvilles-entry/|title=QRL announces Townsville's entry|date=10 September 2014|publisher=|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>
On 14 February 2015, the Blackhawks played their first game at the venue, a 12–24 loss to the [[North Queensland Cowboys]] in a pre-season trial.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nrl.com/news/2015/02/14/cowboys-post-blackhawks-win/|title=Cowboys post Blackhawks win|date=14 February 2015|publisher=|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref> On March 7, they played their first [[Queensland Cup]] at the venue, defeating the [[Mackay Cutters]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.qrl.com.au/news/2015/03/09/blackhawks-warm-up-with-win/|title=Blackhawks warm up with win|date=9 March 2015|publisher=|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>
In 2017, the venue was upgraded with new playing lights thanks to a state government grant. The new 227 [[lux]] lights allowed the venue to host night games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blackhawkstsv.com.au/2017/05/17/see-the-light-at-jack-manski-oval/|title=Switching to a New Light at Jack Manski Oval - Mendi Townsville & Districts Blackhawks RFLC|date=17 May 2017|publisher=|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>
