{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Knowle Cricket Club Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = Knowle cricket club ground.jpg | location = [[Bristol]] | establishment = 1894 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1926-1928 | club1 = [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset]] | date = 30 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/561.html Ground profile }}
'''Knowle Cricket Club Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Bristol]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1894, when Knowle played Frenchay.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/561_misc.html Other matches played on Knowle Cricket Club Ground]</ref> In 1926 the ground held its first [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match when [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset]] played [[Hampshire County Cricket Club|Hampshire]] in the [[County Championship]]. The following season the ground held a further first-class match when Somerset played [[Worcestershire County Cricket Club|Worcestershire]]. The final first-class match held at the ground came in 1928 when Somerset played [[Essex County Cricket Club|Essex]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/561_f.html First-Class matches played on Knowle Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
Still in use to this day, the ground is the home venue of [[Knowle Cricket Club]].<ref>[http://knowle.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp Knowle Cricket Club]</ref>
