The '''Thighmaster''' is an exercise product designed to shape one's [[thighs]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Berkman |first=Meredith |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,310579,00.html |title=Suzanne Somers and the ThighMaster |publisher=EW.com |date=1992-05-22 |accessdate=2015-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Time for a Fitness Pyramid?; After Thigh Master, a Stream of Fitness Gadgets|publisher= The New York Times|date=1995-03-29|url= https://www.nytimes.com/1995/03/29/garden/time-for-a-fitness-pyramid-after-thigh-master-a-stream-of-fitness-gadgets.html?pagewanted=all|accessdate=2010-12-22|first=Molly|last=O'Neill}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= A Meeting Of Behinds With A Thigh Master|publisher= [[Sun Sentinel]]|date=|url= http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/1995-03-08/lifestyle/9503070465_1_workout-fitness-buns|accessdate=2010-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Advice on fitness gadgets: try to exercise restraint fitness experts aren't impressed by most of those items you see advertised on tv - except the butt master.|publisher= [[Orlando Sentinel]]|date=|url= http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1996-01-26/lifestyle/9601240640_1_exercise-physiologist-lisa-richardson-thigh-master|accessdate=2010-12-22}}</ref> The device is basically two pieces of metal tube bent in a loop and connected with a [[hinge]]. The intended use is to put the Thighmaster between the [[knees]] and squeeze them together.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.shape.com/fitness/gear/do-seen-tv-fitness-products-work |title=Suzanne Somers' Thigh Master - As Seen On TV Fitness Products: Do They Work? &#124; Shape Magazine |publisher=Shape.com |date=2012-10-28 |accessdate=2018-10-27 }}</ref> This exercises the [[hip adductors]]. The simple mechanism allows exercising any suitable [[muscle]] where a small angle can be created to press it, for example the [[biceps]] (elbow flexion) or the hamstrings (knee flexion).<ref name="LAtimes">{{cite news|title= Working out old school: Is it time to pull out the ThighMaster?|publisher= [[The Los Angeles Times]]|date=2009-01-05|url= http://articles.latimes.com/2009/jan/05/health/he-retro5|accessdate=2010-12-21|first=Whitney|last=Friedlander}}</ref>
As with most fitness products marketed to homes, advertisements often emphasized that the Thighmaster could be used while doing something else. The [[infomercials]] featured people watching television and exercising with the Thighmaster at the same time. It was mainly advertised in the 1990s by the actress [[Suzanne Somers]].<ref name="LAtimes" /><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://jezebel.com/the-newest-thighmaster-vibrates-is-finally-useful-1699961029 |title=The Newest ThighMaster Vibrates, Is Finally Useful |publisher=Jezebel.com |date= |accessdate=2015-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/17/suzanne-somers-thighmaster_n_7086648.html |title=Suzanne Somers Says Her Vibrating ThighMaster 'Makes Sex More Enjoyable' |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date=2015-04-17 |accessdate=2015-10-22}}</ref>
The Thighmaster was marketed by [[Joshua Reynolds (inventor)|Joshua Reynolds]], who also made a great deal of money with his version of the [[Mood ring]]. Reynolds is an heir to the fortune of [[R. J. Reynolds]], founder of [[R. J. Reynolds Tobacco Company]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1993-03-17/lifestyle/9303150395_1_suzanne-somers-dennis-weaver-thighmaster |title=Inventor Of The Thighmaster Stays On The Ball - tribunedigital-orlandosentinel |publisher=Articles.orlandosentinel.com |date=1993-03-17 |accessdate=2015-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/bieler-540242-thighmaster-says.html |title=O.C. inventor squeezed ThighMaster into American culture |publisher=Ocregister.com |accessdate=2015-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/ekij45h/thigh-master/ |title=Thigh Master - In Photos: 10 Corny But Effective Cable TV Ads |publisher=Forbes |date=1970-01-01 |accessdate=2015-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=A479XLrmk54C&pg=PT41&lpg=PT41&dq=joshua+reynolds+thighmaster&source=bl&ots=9xQU8KSXJT&sig=kFQ1YbyGgqycXGjLH1M9F80hb1M&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CB8Q6AEwADgKahUKEwik2NyXw9XIAhUGTBQKHVPZCAU#v=onepage&q=joshua%20reynolds%20thighmaster&f=false |title=The Indispensable Book of Useless Information: Just When You Thought It ... - Don Voorhees |publisher=Books.google.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.advancedphysicalmedicine.org/blog/2013/02/18/debunking-4-popular-exercise-fads/ |title=Debunking 4 Popular Exercise Fads – Advanced Physical Medicine |publisher=Advancedphysicalmedicine.org |date=2013-02-18 |accessdate=2015-10-22}}</ref>
